        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 5:34AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 534 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Franklin, or 10 miles southeast of Nantahala Lake,
moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Highlands, Scaly Mountain, Cashiers, Otto, Rainbow Springs, Whiteside
Mountain, Cullasaja, Franklin, Ellijay, and Bad Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon EDT for
northeastern Georgia...western North Carolina...and Upstate South
Carolina.</instruction>
